CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1961, pg. A10 reads: "Charming Pair- Mrs. Eric Springer, left, entertained at a delightful "at home" last Sunday afternoon, honoring her mother, Mrs. Chloe Kennedy of Brooklyn, N.Y. The charming pair are pictured on the veranda of the Springer home.  A heavy-loaded apple tree is in background. - Harris photo."Related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 8, 1967, pg. 14, to illustrate article titled: "Cecile Springer to Chair Women Voter's State Meet."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Cecile Springer and her mother, Chloe Kennedy, standing on patio behind plant
